                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14455986" author="agudian" created="Sat, 5 Oct 2013 10:45:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I would expect that for each test method, the actual wall-clock time is reported, and that the sum for the test class is the sum of the test method times.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What exactly does your report file show?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456140" author="krosenvold" created="Sat, 5 Oct 2013 12:40:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We have a long tradition for breaking elapsed time calculation every now and then &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; Did you actually check that this  first broke in 2.15 this time ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The execution calculation time is (unfortunately) fairly convoluted and not /easily/ testable. I suppose it&apos;s about time we face the challenge though &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; Maybe an IT that does 3-4 parallel &quot;reallySleep(0.1, 0.5,1,2)&quot; and we can assert that the run-time is within &quot;acceptable&quot; limits. The problem is always understanding &quot;what&quot; acceptable limits are, since reallSleep(0.1) can easily sleep for 0.5 every now and then, which gives unreliable tests.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe there&apos;s some kind of unit test we can make.....&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14456002" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Sun, 6 Oct 2013 08:29:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The individual sleep threads could check that their sleep is within limits, and/or perhaps report back their actual elapsed time?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456137" author="tibor17" created="Fri, 29 Aug 2014 18:28:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;br/&gt;
I would also like to have a real time spent by class in the report.&lt;br/&gt;
For me the sum of time-overlapping methods is not valuable because i don&apos;t know how long the test was really running.&lt;br/&gt;
As far as I remember we sum the partial method exec time.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14537376" author="tibor17" created="Sun, 10 May 2015 21:17:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;commit c14b25fe501193ce5779ff7d5da2590164ca7b8e&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
